// 1.	cpio: Creates or extracts archives. Commonly used with pipes to copy files in and out of cpio or tar archives.
// 2.	sort: Sorts lines of text files. Useful for organizing data alphabetically or numerically. Can be applied to files or command outputs.
// 3.	fuser: Displays process IDs using a specified file, file system, or socket. Can also be used to kill processes accessing a particular resource.
// 4.	file: Determines the type of a file by examining its content. Outputs information about the file format or type, helping identify file characteristics
